      "comment_id" : 40960567,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "As Andreas has noted, there&#39;s no <i>rules</i> about using upper casing in package names.  One specific reason to avoid it is that I have seen people run into problems with mixed case package names when doing cross platform development.  Especially when someone decides to rename or change the case of a package, you&#39;re then relying on both your VCS and development environments to do <i>exactly</i> the right thing with the directory case."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
