      "post_id" : 3179277,
      "comment_id" : 33735421,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Here: <a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/codeconventions-135099.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">oracle.com/technetwork/java/codeconventions-135099.html</a> it says all-lower, but here <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-6.html#jls-6.1\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-6.html#jls-6.1</a> it says that the first component should be in lower case, also they removed examples of upper case word separation. Also here: <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/package/namingpkgs.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/package/namingpkgs.html</a> it says all-lower case. So it seems that upper case in package names is currently discouraged."
