    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Anyone can use underscores (it's okay).</p>\n<p>No one should use hyphens (it's bad practice and it may result in errors as per @glglgl in the comments section).</p>\n<p>No one should use capital letters inside package names (bad practice).</p>\n<p><em>Note: Here, &quot;bad practice&quot; means that technically you are allowed to use that, but conventionally it's not well-mannered to do so.</em></p>\n<p>Source: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/package/namingpkgs.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Naming a Package (docs.oracle)</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/R2HcY.png\" alt=\"table on how to legalize package names in Java\" /></p>\n"
